      <title>Daily Security News from @trustpath - Dec 28, 2016</title>
      <link>//cloudfeed.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2016-12-28/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 28 Dec 2016 18:05:01 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>//cloudfeed.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2016-12-28/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Daily Security news from &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/trustpath&#34;&gt;@trustpath&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;New cybersecurity survey says spending is misdirected and unclear&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nearly four in five respondents (79 percent) said they had increased spending on data breach detection in the past year and 72 percent said they &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.securityinfowatch.com/press_release/12290288/new-cybersecurity-survey-says-spending-is-misdirected-and-unclear&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.securityinfowatch.com/press_release/12290288/new-cybersecurity-survey-says-spending-is-misdirected-and-unclear&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;New cybersecurity survey says spending is misdirected and unclear&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, a majority of respondents (52 percent) said preventing data breaches was their top spending priority, while 42 percent said detection was &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.securityinfowatch.com/press_release/12290288/new-cybersecurity-survey-says-spending-is-misdirected-and-unclear&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.securityinfowatch.com/press_release/12290288/new-cybersecurity-survey-says-spending-is-misdirected-and-unclear&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Everything You Need To Know About Endpoint Protection And Why It&amp;rsquo;s&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DABCC.com The short answer to the question about needing endpoint protection is that if you, or your employees, access your network or system through any type &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dabcc.com/everything-you-need-to-know-about-endpoint-protection-and-why-its-important-to-your-business/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.dabcc.com/everything-you-need-to-know-about-endpoint-protection-and-why-its-important-to-your-business/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;York schools at risk of serious data breaches, inspection reveals&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AUDITORS have found big gaps in the way York schools deal with personal information about pupils and staff. A survey of 20 schools was carried out &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/14986442.York_schools_at_risk_of_serious_data_breaches__inspection_reveals/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/news/14986442.York_schools_at_risk_of_serious_data_breaches__inspection_reveals/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;How To Minimize Insider Threats In Cyber Security&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apart from the famous NSA leak by Edward Snowden, there are also strong rumors that several high profile data breaches and leaks of the past &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.informationsecuritybuzz.com/articles/minimize-insider-threats-cyber-security/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.informationsecuritybuzz.com/articles/minimize-insider-threats-cyber-security/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;School district should offer five years&amp;rsquo; ID protection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;hellip; stolen in an attack on the university&amp;rsquo;s system two years ago in what has been called one of the largest data breaches to occur at a U.S. university.  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.fredericknewspost.com/opinion/editorial/school-district-should-offer-five-years-id-protection/article_9c88e66f-111e-5b9d-b9eb-1ba96bc0b35d.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.fredericknewspost.com/opinion/editorial/school-district-should-offer-five-years-id-protection/article_9c88e66f-111e-5b9d-b9eb-1ba96bc0b35d.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Worldwide Physical Security Market to Soar at 14.9% CAGR thanks to Rising&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;openPR (press release) &amp;hellip; physical security market is classified into management analysis and modeling software and physical security information management (PSIM).  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.openpr.com/news/402513/Worldwide-Physical-Security-Market-to-Soar-at-14-9-CAGR-thanks-to-Rising-Adoption-Biometric-Access-Control-Segment.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.openpr.com/news/402513/Worldwide-Physical-Security-Market-to-Soar-at-14-9-CAGR-thanks-to-Rising-Adoption-Biometric-Access-Control-Segment.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Verizon Expected To Move Ahead With Yahoo Deal&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Identity Theft Resource Center, which Bloomberg cited in its report, pegs the number of data breaches in the U.S. at close to 1,000 this year alone, &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.pymnts.com/news/partnerships-acquisitions/2016/verizon-expected-to-move-ahead-with-yahoo-deal/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.pymnts.com/news/partnerships-acquisitions/2016/verizon-expected-to-move-ahead-with-yahoo-deal/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Learning From A Year of Security Breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This year (2016) I accepted as much incident response work as I could. I spent about 300 hours responding to security incidents and data breaches &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linux.com/news/learning-year-security-breaches&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.linux.com/news/learning-year-security-breaches&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;The 10 Biggest Data Breaches Of 2016&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another year, another collection of massive data breaches. While 2015 had some massive breaches, 2016 proved worse, with two of the largest data &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.crn.com/slide-shows/security/300083246/the-10-biggest-data-breaches-of-2016.htm&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.crn.com/slide-shows/security/300083246/the-10-biggest-data-breaches-of-2016.htm&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Bring Your Own Device: To Be, or Not to Be?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In view of this grim security outlook, 97% of CIOs are looking at new ways to secure their company from data breaches. But how does one essentially &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.readitquik.com/articles/hrtech/bring-your-own-device-to-be-or-not-to-be/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.readitquik.com/articles/hrtech/bring-your-own-device-to-be-or-not-to-be/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Securing 2017: Predictions for the year ahead&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data breaches, malware infections, and social engineering attacks have become common and almost expected. Unfortunately, all signs point to this &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.securityinfowatch.com/article/12290424/securing-2017-predictions-for-the-year-ahead&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.securityinfowatch.com/article/12290424/securing-2017-predictions-for-the-year-ahead&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Lack of Funds Hinders Cyberattack Prevention, Analysts Say&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The breach is the most recent in a series of data breaches and hacks affecting public agencies and companies. However, funding concerns may have &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.bna.com/lack-funds-hinders-n73014449114/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.bna.com/lack-funds-hinders-n73014449114/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Improving Threat Hunting with Managed Security Services&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wednesday December 28, 2016. Our Guide to Threat Hunting series &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://digitalguardian.com/blog/improving-threat-hunting-managed-security-services&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://digitalguardian.com/blog/improving-threat-hunting-managed-security-services&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Authorities worry public may be lured into illegal activities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The messages account for 80 per cent of all complaints received by the commission, including those related to personal data breaches. Although this &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.tnp.sg/news/singapore/authorities-worry-public-may-be-lured-illegal-activities&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.tnp.sg/news/singapore/authorities-worry-public-may-be-lured-illegal-activities&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;EDITORIAL: Scanning of licenses needs limits&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In a world where privacy has been so eroded that massive data breaches now make us shrug instead of shudderunless we&amp;rsquo;re directly a victimthe &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dailyprogress.com/starexponent/opinion/editorial-scanning-of-licenses-needs-limits/article_40c93286-ee03-5f61-9161-8a9f93bd21dd.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.dailyprogress.com/starexponent/opinion/editorial-scanning-of-licenses-needs-limits/article_40c93286-ee03-5f61-9161-8a9f93bd21dd.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Will Massive Data Breaches Lead Verizon To Dump Yahoo?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s because the public is getting so used to the idea of hacks and data breaches, it doesn&amp;rsquo;t seem like a major event anymore. Eventually, everyone &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://consumerist.com/2016/12/28/will-massive-data-breaches-lead-verizon-to-dump-yahoo/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://consumerist.com/2016/12/28/will-massive-data-breaches-lead-verizon-to-dump-yahoo/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Top 10 Data Breaches in 2016&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s a recap of the top 10 data breaches this year. The list includes the biggest ones that happened and reported or disclosed within the year.  &lt;a href=&#34;http://techwireasia.com/2016/12/top-10-data-breaches-2016/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://techwireasia.com/2016/12/top-10-data-breaches-2016/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
